President Donald J. Trump issued a proclamation on January 18, 2019, marking the Martin Luther King, Jr. Federal Holiday. The proclamation acknowledges the significance of Dr. King's vision for equality and justice in America and encourages all citizens to engage in acts of service to their community and the nation. President Trump also highlights the progress made in job creation and criminal justice reform, while acknowledging that more work needs to be done to fulfill Dr. King's dream. The proclamation reaffirms the commitment to expanding opportunities for all Americans and honoring the legacy of Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr.